cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.MM

This paper deals with image processing techniques using deep learning models, specifically Super Resolution Convolutional Neural Networks (SRCNN), to enhance the resolution of digital rock images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves image segmentation and noise reduction, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) respectively. Additionally, the paper deals with micro-computed tomography (μCT) images, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
